HEADWORD: Contemptuously
<hw>Con*temp"tu*ous*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a contemptuous
manner; with scorn or disdain; despitefully.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The apostles and most eminent Christians were poor, and used
<qex>contemptuously</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contemptuousness</ent>⟦br⟧
